{
  "stem": "1895.4",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "This camp was-- as I said, it's a terrible place and epidemics would break out periodically.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And one of the epidemics I fell victim to, a typhus epidemic, and I got sick.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And after [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] coming down with the sickness, you know, maybe one out of three survived once you contracted the sickness.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But I made it through because of help of some people who helped me.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I remember there was a fellow by the name of Saul Mincberg, who was one of the inmate administrators of the camp, who helped me after my sickness.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And for some reason, he was very good to me.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And this human exchange, you know, and the fact that not everybody is so bad, that gave me hope.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And it helped a great deal.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And he brought me in, and he gave me another job in Blizyn.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And he helped me out.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "He took me to the kitchen after my sickness.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And he told the cook to give me extra rations every day until I recovered.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "It was things like this in the camp that a young man of-- like of my age was able to start life anew, get new hope, and get going again, and face whatever was coming one more time.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "We stayed in Blizyn until the summer of 1944.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "The summer of 1944, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] the Germans begin to evacuate the area, because the Russian armies were coming close on the eastern side.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And in the summer of 1944, we were taken-- one morning we were taken to the rail station in Blizyn and loaded into freight cars.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And I remember going over to one of the mesh pockets of the rail car.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
